  "text": "Northern analyses of regions isolated from mouse brain were performed using the 5′ and 3′ oligonucleotides complementary to the human Fe65 cDNA to probe duplicate samples. These studies reveal that Fe65 is expressed in all of the brain regions analyzed: hippocampus/amygdala, hypothalamus, frontal cortex, cerebellum, and olfactory bulb (not shown). These results are entirely consistent with the in situ data and suggest widespread expression of Fe65 in the brain. Our results, in addition to the previous description of Fe65 expression in the embryonic central nervous system [CITATION_1] , suggest that Fe65 expression persists throughout development.",
